The authority to which an appeal against an order imposing any of the penalties specified in rule 6 lies may, of its own motion or otherwise, call for the record of any  proceeding under these rules and review any order passed in such a case and, may,after consultation with the Commission where such consultation is necessary, pass such orders as it deems fit as if the Government servant had preferred an appeal against such order;
   that no action under this rule shall be taken after the expiry of a period of more than six months from the date of such order
